The two men who were apparently trapped in the wreckage of a structural collapse at a construction site in Sandton have been rushed to hospital. (ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The two men who were apparently trapped in the wreckage of a structural collapse at a construction site in Sandton on Tuesday have been rushed to hospital, paramedics said. &nbsp; "On inspection, paramedics discovered that two men had fallen through some scaffolding."READ: Two trapped in Sandton construction wreckage"Paramedics immediately assessed both men and found that they were in a critical condition, having sustained numerous injuries," ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said."Once treated, the patients were transported to a nearby private hospital for urgent treatment, one by ER24 and the second by another private service."Emer-G-Med said earlier that the two were trapped inside the wreckage.The cause of the collapse was being investigated.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.